claim.claim-text:
1. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature, wherein the mechanical coupling between the solder member and the contact member comprises the sole means of attachment; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface.

17. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature, wherein the solder member comprises a snap-fit relationship with the engagement features; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface.

18. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature, wherein the solder member is free-floating relative to the contact member; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface.

19. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature, wherein the engagement feature comprises one of a hole, a recess, a protrusion, or a barb mechanically coupled to the solder member;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface.

20. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature, wherein the engagement feature is plastically or elastically deformed into engagement with the solder member;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface.

21. An electrical interconnect assembly for electrically interconnecting terminals on a first circuit member with terminals on a second circuit member, the electrical interconnect assembly comprising:
a housing comprising a plurality of through openings that extend between a first surface and a second surface of the housing;
a plurality of contact members positioned in a plurality of the through openings, the contact members comprising;
a base portion;
one or more beams having a proximal end attached to the base portion and a distal end extending away from the base portion generally in a first direction;
one or more tabs attached to the base portion extending away from the base portion generally in a second direction, the tabs comprising at least one engagement feature;

a solder member mechanically coupled with the engagement feature; and
a sealing layer on the housing that substantially prevents solder from wicking between the contact members and the housing, and from the first surface and the second surface, the sealing layer comprising a flowable, curable polymeric material molded to the housing.
